      "writtenOn": "2021-07-16T14:56:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh wait - is this interacting with the changes in SkVMBlitter? How? We\u0027re updating the buffer held by the Uniforms object that was present when we were created, but the blitter code is now allocating a separate buffer. Are we even updating the right one? Wondering if this pattern would be safer/better if we didn\u0027t take the Uniforms object in the constructor, and it was instead passed to the update() - so the updater object is told: \"Here\u0027s the uniform block, do any patching you need.\"",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 416,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 416,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "c089606adfe667a277e8de8aea7559e42e876c3d",
